         <div type="edition" xml:lang="okz-Latn">
           <p><lb n="1"/><g type="ddandaOrnate"/> <num value="834">834</num> śaka n<supplied reason="lost">u</supplied> mrateñ· sāṅ·barṇa <placeName type="settlement" subtype="town" key="Bhavapura">bhaba<add place="above">pura</add></placeName> <add place="above">nā</add> dau qmuṁ cas· sruk· <placeName type="settlement" subtype="village" key="Citrasiṅ">citrasiṅ·</placeName> jvan· bhūmi <placeName type="region" subtype="land">samañ<supplied reason="omitted">·</supplied></placeName> ta vraḥ kaṁmrateṅ<supplied reason="omitted">·</supplied> Añ<supplied reason="omitted">·</supplied> śivali<add place="above">ṅ</add>ga</p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
               <listApp>
                 <app loc="A1">
                     <lem>citrasiṅ·</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Coedes1937-1966_01">citraliṅ</rdg>
                 </app>
               </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="fra" resp="part:sapi">
 	         <p n="1">En 834 Śaka, le <foreign>mrateñ</foreign> Sāṅvarṇa de Bhavapura, quand il alla à l'ancien point de rendez-vous <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>qmuṁ cas</foreign>, au vieux coin</supplied> du village de Citrasiṅ, a offert la terre de Samañ au <foreign>vraḥ kamrateṅ añ</foreign> Śivaliṅga.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="fra" source="bib:Coedes1937-1966_01">
           <p n="1">En 834 śaka, Mrateñ Sāṅvarṇa de Bhavapura, lorsqu'il allait à Amuṁ Cas <supplied reason="explanation">"le vieux coin"</supplied> dans le pays de Citraliṅ, a donné la terre de Samañ à V.K.A. Śivaliṅga.</p>
           </div>
         <div type="commentary">
          <p>This inscription is a later addition to the Southern Doorjamb. It was engraved on the side of this inscription, from top to bottom.</p>
         </div>
